Phishing Risk Analysis

Our analysis of the URL https://ummjkgha.top/sbisec/ indicates a high risk of phishing, with a risk score of 85. This suggests the URL is likely a fraudulent attempt to steal your personal information.

Key Risk Indicators

    • Suspicious Domain Name: The domain name "ummjkgha.top" is highly unusual and appears randomly generated. Legitimate organizations typically use recognizable and relevant domain names. This random string of characters is a strong indicator of a potentially malicious website.
      • Uncommon Top-Level Domain (TLD): The use of the ".top" TLD is another red flag. While not inherently malicious, it's less common for reputable organizations and often favored by malicious actors due to lower registration costs and less stringent oversight.
        • Low Time-To-Live (TTL) Hostname: The TTL hostname value of 1 is unusually low. This could indicate that the domain's DNS records are being frequently updated, a tactic sometimes used by malicious actors to evade detection or quickly switch server locations.
          • Zero MX Servers: The absence of MX records (qty_mx_servers: 0) indicates that the domain isn't configured to receive emails. This is unusual for legitimate businesses and further raises suspicion about the website's legitimacy.
            • Not Indexed by Google: Both the domain and URL are not indexed by Google (domain_google_index: 0, url_google_index: 0). While new websites may take time to be indexed, the combination of this factor with the others strengthens the case for phishing.

          Technical Assessment

          The URL "https://ummjkgha.top/sbisec/" exhibits several technical characteristics that contribute to its high-risk assessment. The domain name "ummjkgha.top" is 12 characters long and uses an uncommon TLD. The directory "/sbisec/" might be an attempt to mimic a legitimate organization, potentially SBI Securities, to deceive users. The absence of MX servers suggests a lack of genuine email communication infrastructure. The low TTL value for the hostname and the lack of Google indexing further point towards a potentially malicious setup. While the presence of an SSL certificate (tls_ssl_certificate: 1) might give a false sense of security, phishing sites are increasingly using HTTPS to appear more legitimate.

          What This Means For You

          If this website is indeed a phishing site, interacting with it could lead to several serious consequences. Entering any personal information, such as login credentials, financial details, or personal identification, could be stolen by the attackers. This information could then be used for identity theft, financial fraud, or other malicious activities. Simply visiting the site could potentially expose your device to malware.

          Recommended Actions

            • Do not click on the link: Avoid accessing this URL under any circumstances.
              • Report the suspicious URL: Report the URL to PhishGuard and your email provider to help prevent others from falling victim.
                • Warn others: If you received this link in an email or message, inform the sender that it's suspicious and warn others not to click on it.
                  • Check your online accounts: If you have already visited the website and entered any information, immediately change your passwords for all affected accounts and monitor your financial statements for any unauthorized activity.
